    <main>
      <h1>Greetings from the Crustaceans</h1>
      <p>This postcard is printed on sand-colored stock: think Tahiti shimmer, Bahamas breezes, Florida palms, and tiny crustaceans tracing the shoreline in coffee-splattered ink. OpenClaw is your main pier, and the view now stretches along every nano- and pico-powered beach.</p>

      <section>
        <h2>What are people doing with all these crustaceans?</h2>
        <p>OpenClaw, NanoClaw, PicoClaw, NemoClaw, and the rest of the flotilla are being pressed into service across sunlit labs and nostalgic coffee bars. They stream retro postcard tutorials, anchor micro-containers by the surf, and keep archival sand journals for every new idea.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>OpenClaw</strong> orchestrates the fleet, coordinating deployments from the main pier while tasting a dark roast beside the command console.</li>
          <li><strong>NanoClaw</strong> is the alpine shell tucked under a beach umbrella—lightweight, portable, great for tasting oceanic espresso shots.</li>
          <li><strong>PicoClaw</strong> fits in your palm like a polished shell, letting you pilot custom scripts between cabana sketches.</li>
          <li><strong>NemoClaw</strong> dives deep, collecting logs in glass bottles and sending them to the bayfront archives.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Your crew adds new stamps for each deployment: the more you share, the richer the travel ledger of crustaceans.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>This is how you set one up</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Start with a French press pour—let the beans bloom as you sketch the shoreline of your plan.</li>
          <li>Follow the OpenClaw quickstart (see <a href="https://openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the docs</a>), spark your worker deploy, and sprinkle the layout with postcard-style art and coffee hues.</li>
          <li>Anchor the project on Cloudflare Workers: a clean CNAME to `crustaceans-sh.mitdaphne.workers.dev` and the custom domain will ride the gentle tide.</li>
          <li>Take a screenshot of the view, stamp it “Clean workshop, organized,” and share it with the crew so everyone can sip the same brew.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Postcard rack</h2>
        <p>Keep this site updated with fresh beaches, new clues about the OpenClaw family (Nano, Pico, Nemo), and more coffee-themed dispatches. Drop a note on GitHub when you want another postcard, and I’ll pin it to the rack.</p>
      </section>
